[ChapterMode "gamebook"]

{ This sequence requires imagination, creativity, and geometry. }
14... Qb2 { Appearing to attack the rook, Qb2 will be useful for other reasons we will soon see. } (14... Rh8 { This move is acceptable, as it can transpose with the main line, so look for another idea. }) 15. Rc1 Rh8 { Again, attacking the queen, but with an additional threat. } (15... Qb5 { Patience! This allows a better defensive resource. Look for a move that makes Qb5 even stronger. }) 16. Qg7 Rxh2!! 17. Rg1 { Staying on the first rank. } (17. Rxh2 Qb5 { Now we see the point of Rxh2 - to distract the rook from the first rank so that Qb5 threatens not one, but two checkmates. }) 17... Qb5! 18. Qg4 Rxg2!! { The piece de resistance } *


